.TH "clk_hw_create_clk" 9 "clk_hw_create_clk" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clk_hw_create_clk \- Allocate and link a clk consumer to a clk_core given a clk_hw
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct clk *" clk_hw_create_clk
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct clk_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "const char *dev_id "  ","
.BI "const char *con_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
clk consumer device
.IP "hw" 12
clk_hw associated with the clk being consumed
.IP "dev_id" 12
string describing device name
.IP "con_id" 12
connection ID string on device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is the main function used to create a clk pointer for use by clk
consumers. It connects a consumer to the clk_core and clk_hw structures
used by the framework and clk provider respectively.
